HEADWORD: guama
<hw>guama</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A tropical tree of Central America and
the West Indies and Puerto Rico (<spn>Inga laurina</spn>) having spikes
of white flowers; it is used as shade for coffee plantations.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> <spn>Inga laurina</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
